---

Self-driving cars were approved in San Francisco, a city sometimes seen as being risk-averse and somewhat hostile to the tech sector. 

And they lack approvals in many other cities. 

## How did Waymo succeed in getting permission in San Francisco, and what are the regulatory and economic barriers to self-driving cars being approved and deployed in other cities across America and the world?
